description.narrative: UNICEF Bolivia had a successful year in terms of mobilizing resources to achieve results for children and adolescents. The office reached US$7,044,000 in 2021 – 41% above the US$5 million target. This was possible thanks to a diversified fundraising strategy and important partnerships that provide funds for both development and humanitarian programming. The country office also achieved an important milestone in terms of individual giving: it was the first UNICEF ‘frontier market office’ globally to reach 5,000 active individual pledge donors thanks to an effective strategy and a highly prepared team (5,800 donors by the end of the year). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/12/2021
